The Wave;;2008;;Not Rated;;Drama,Thriller;;7.6;;Dennis Gansel;;Jürgen Vogel,Frederick Lau,Max Riemelt,Jennifer Ulrich,Christiane Paul,Jacob Matschenz,Cristina do Rego,Elyas M'Barek,Maximilian Vollmar,Max Mauff,Ferdinand Schmidt-Modrow,Tim Oliver Schultz,Amelie Kiefer,Fabian Preger,Odine Johne,Tino Mewes,Karoline Teska,Marco Bretscher-Coschignano;;When Rainer Wegner (Jürgen Vogel), a popular high school teacher, finds himself relegated to teaching autocracy, instead of anarchy, as part of the school's project week, he is less than enthusiastic. So are his students, who greet the prospect of studying fascism yet again with apathetic grumbling: The Nazis sucked. We get it. Struck by the teenagers complacency and unwitting arrogance, Rainer devises an unorthodox experiment. But his hastily conceived lesson in social orders and the power of unity soon grows a life of its own.;;https://www.imdb.com/title/tt1063669/